	doi = {10.1101/2025.06.20.25329138},
	abstract = {Importance Polygenic background modifies variant penetrance in hypertrophic (HCM) and dilated (DCM) cardiomyopathy, diseases with opposing morphologic characteristics and inversely related genetic pathways. Whether polygenic susceptibility for one disease protects against monogenic risk for the other remains unexplored.
Objective To characterize if polygenic background bidirectionally modifies pathogenicity of established rare variants associated with HCM and DCM.
